data.desc:
proposed names reference concepts of measurement, time, and origins: 
- "Kaliber" derives from caliber, denoting measurement and precision; 
- "Axion" references the Greek concept of the temporal axis; 
- "Sothis" invokes the ancient Egyptian star used as a temporal reference point; 
- "Archè" employs the Greek term for principle or beginning; 
- "Chronodex" compounds temporal indexing; and "Kairos" signifies the Greek notion of the opportune moment.

These naming options reflect a conceptual framework that positions the device within historical traditions of time measurement and philosophical approaches to temporality, suggesting the artifact's role in mediating temporal experience through measurement.
